import { useState } from "react"
import Button from 'react-bootstrap/Button';
import Form from 'react-bootstrap/Form';
import { Alert, Col, Container, Row } from "react-bootstrap";
import 'bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css';

const SignUp = () => {
    const [email,setEmail] = useState('')
    const [password,setPassword] = useState('')
    const [error,setError] = useState('')
    const [loading,setLoading] = useState(false)

   const signingUpHandler = (e) =>{
      e.preventDefault()

      console.log("email: "+email+" password: "+password)
   }


    return (
      <Container fluid className="bg-light" >

        

        <Form onSubmit={signingUpHandler}>
        
          <Row className="justify-content-md-center">
          <Alert className="mb-3" variant="warning">
            Test test
          </Alert>
            <Col md="12">
              <Form.Group className="mb-3" controlId="formBasicEmail">
                <Form.Label>Email address</Form.Label>
                <Form.Control type="email" placeholder="Enter email" onChange={setEmail} />
              </Form.Group>
            </Col>
  
            <Col md="12">
              <Form.Group className="mb-3" controlId="formPassword">
                <Form.Label>Password</Form.Label>
                <Form.Control type="password" placeholder="Password" onChange={setPassword} />
              </Form.Group>
            </Col>
            <Col md="12">
              <Form.Group className="mb-3" controlId="formPassword">
                <Form.Label>Password</Form.Label>
                <Form.Control type="password" placeholder="Confirm Password" onChange={setPassword} />
              </Form.Group>
            </Col>
            <Col >
                <Button className="w-100" variant="primary" type="submit">
                  Submit
                </Button>
            </Col>

        </Row>
        
      </Form>
      </Container>
    )
}

export default SignUp
